' @id(CMP-VIEWER-SHELL)
' @ref(USE-VIEW-DIAGRAMS)
' @desc(CMP-VIEWER-SHELL, "The egui shell of mdd-viewer as built by MddViewer::update: collapsible left/right SidePanels, a toolbar with no zoom buttons, the center-fixed fisheye canvas stage that warps the rendered texture before painting, and a per-frame theming step that delegates to CMP-VIEWER-THEME (theme.rs).")
' @id(CMP-MOCKUP-LAUNCH)
' @ref(USE-OPEN-RENDER)
' @desc(CMP-MOCKUP-LAUNCH, "As built (crates/mdd-viewer/src/lib.rs): the launch helpers behind the view-tab 'Open render' button. selected_render_slug() gates the button; open_mockup_render(root, slug) spawns a thread that calls mockup_server_up() to probe localhost:4317, spawns npm run dev with cwd <root>/mockups only if the port is not serving (polling until it binds), then open_in_browser opens the OS default browser at /mockup/<slug>. No npm install, no child-process shutdown tracking.")
' Current-side component view derived from MddViewer::update in
' crates/mdd-viewer/src/lib.rs. Chrome theming is owned by
' CMP-VIEWER-THEME (theme.rs).
title mdd-viewer UI shell — ownership (current)

actor "Developer" as Dev <<added>>

component "MddViewer\n(eframe::App)\nupdate()" as Viewer
component "SidePanel left\n\"rail\" / sliver" as Left
component "SidePanel right\n\"context\" / sliver" as Right
component "svg_toolbar\n(PAGE selector + hint;\nno Reset/Zoom+/Zoom-)" as Toolbar
component "Fisheye canvas stage\nCanvasView::fisheye_mesh" as Fisheye
component "PanelLayout" as PL
component "CanvasView" as CV
component "eframe / egui 0.30\npainter.add(Shape::mesh)" as Egui
component "Theme module\n(theme.rs,\nCMP-VIEWER-THEME)" as Theme

Dev --> Viewer : mdd view
Viewer --> Theme : theme::register_fonts(&cc.egui_ctx) once\n+ theme::apply_theme(ctx) first per frame
Theme --> Egui : FontDefinitions + Visuals + Style overrides
Viewer --> Left : draw + collapse chevron / sliver
Viewer --> Right : draw + collapse chevron / sliver
Left --> PL : toggle_left()
Right --> PL : toggle_right()
Viewer --> Toolbar : draw (no zoom controls)
Viewer --> Fisheye : warp rendered texture per frame
Fisheye --> CV : focal=centre, strength, radius, warp()
Viewer --> Egui : textured Mesh, clipped to canvas rect
Egui --> Dev : centre-magnified diagram, collapsible panels

note bottom of Fisheye
  The fisheye is a display-time stage on top of the base
  zoom/pan placement; it does not change the render/font
  pipeline (CMP-VIEWER-RENDER-PIPELINE) — it only remaps
  where the already-rasterized texture is painted.
end note

component "MockupLauncher\n(CMP-MOCKUP-LAUNCH)\nopen_mockup_render · mockup_server_up · open_in_browser" as Launch
component "npm run dev\n(Vite dev server, :4317, cwd mockups/)" as Vite
component "OS default browser\n(open / xdg-open / start)" as Browser

Viewer --> Launch : open_mockup_render(root, slug)\non "Open render" click (UIC-OPEN-RENDER)
Launch --> Vite : spawn in mockups/ only if :4317 not serving
Launch --> Browser : open /mockup/<slug>

note bottom of Launch
  Code (CMP-MOCKUP-LAUNCH / USE-OPEN-RENDER): selected_render_slug()
  enables the button only for a ModelKind::Mockup whose
  mockups/src/mockups/<slug>.tsx exists. open_mockup_render runs
  off the UI thread (std::thread): mockup_server_up() probes :4317,
  spawns npm run dev (cwd <root>/mockups) if down and polls until it
  binds, then open_in_browser opens /mockup/<slug>. Realized by
  SEQ-OPEN-RENDER.
end note
@enduml
